abstract: Australian Electoral Commission predicts that Prime Min Malcolm Turnbull and his Liberal-led conservative coalition has won national election over opposition Labor Party, potentially giving them absolute majority of 76 seats.
lead_paragraph: The electoral commission has forecast that Mr. Turnbull’s Liberal Party-led coalition could win a combined 76 seats, which would give it an absolute majority.

headline.main: Malcolm Turnbull Claims Victory in Australia Election After Rival Concedes
headline.print_headline: Australian Stalemate Broken as Premier Declares Election Victory
